is the rising value of indian rupee give india great advantage or not you must have heard about the rising value of indian rupee hoe does it affect india and its people what are the demerits of this situation a strengthening currency has both good points and bad points for example a stronger currency will mean that exported goods have become more expensive in those markets and so it will hurt indian exporters it will also hurt the call centre and technical outsourcing fields which india has been so successful with in the past several years as companies from outside india will be paying more in their local currency at the same time it is good for importers and consumers as imported goods are becoming less expensive in the local currency and importers are paying less in their local currency likewise it makes tourists less interested in visiting but allows local residents to leave and visit other countries less expensively Outsourcing Economy of India Offshoring Gross domestic product Pakistan Economy of Pakistan Trade India Supply and demand Indian Rupee Deflation (economics) Inflation Economy of Africa Indian nationality law Currency Capitalism Indian general elections, 2004 Bretton Woods system Economy of Israel Economy of Sri Lanka Canadian dollar Economic relations of Japan Economy of the United States Japan-United States relations Economic history of Britain Globalization Economy of Venezuela Economy of Chile Argentine economic crisis (1999-2002) Balassa-Samuelson effect Protectionism Government debt Bhutan Economy of Nepal Monetary policy Economy of Nigeria Nepal Compendium of postage stamp issuers (Brit - British) Economy of Macau Shrimp farm Free trade Economy of Belgium Famine Sri Lanka Exchange rate Financial markets Bond Hyperinflation Mutual fund Marshall Plan Economy of Cuba Pound sterling Anarchist economics Argentine Currency Board History of international trade Economy of Russia History of the United States (1789-1849) History of Brazil (1889-1930) Nat